          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Thermistors are resistors that change resistance with temperature. The most common are Negative Temperature",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Coefficient, or NTC, thermistors. The resistance of an NTC thermistor decreases as the temperature increases,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "roughly but not exactly following ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "R = k\/θ",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ". The graph above shows the relationship between resistance and temperature",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "One example of using thermistors or similar devices that vary resistance is a voltage divider, covered in ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/D.C.-Circuits",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : ".",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The output voltage can then be processed using ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Comparator-timer-and-counter-circuits#Comparator",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : "s and",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "doc:\/\/Notes\/documentation\/Notes\/Bipolar-Junction-Transistors",
